title.narrative: Strengthened health system capacity to provide integrated management of severe acute malnutrition

description.narrative: While treatment of children with severe acute malnutrition (SAM) is stagnating in Tanzania at about 13% of the estimated caseload, increased coverage of preventive services contributed to reduction in SAM prevalence and burden from 0.9% (105,000 children) in 2014, to 0.4% (90,000 children) in 2018. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:06/01/2020
